Class Room

java.lang.Object
Room
class Room extends Object
Represents an individual room of the map. Also contains a static method to load all the rooms of the map

  • Field Details

    • room

      private final EnumMap<Direction,Room> room
      Key-value pairs that map each Direction constant to the appropriate Room instance.

    • door

      private final boolean[] door
      Represents the existence of a door at each Direction of this Room instance. The indices of the array correspond to the ordinal numbers of the Direction constants.

    • isExit

      final boolean isExit
      true if this Room is the exit of the labyrinth, else false.

  • Constructor Details

    • Room

      private Room(int row, int col, int[][][] map)
      Constructs a Room instance at the (row,col) position of the given map, setting the right values of the door and isExit fields.
      Parameters:
      row - the number of the row of the given map that contains this Room.
      col - the number of the column of the given map that contains this Room.
      map - the map that encodes as 1 or 0 the existence or not respectively of a door at each Direction of each Room.

  • Method Details

    • getRoomAt

      Room getRoomAt(Direction direction)
      Returns the Room instance at the given direction

    • connectAdjacentRooms

      private void connectAdjacentRooms(int row, int col, Room[][] map)
      Updates the room field with all 4 appropriate connections between this Room and its adjacent Room instances. After this method is executed, this.room.get(direction) evaluates to the Room instance at the direction from this Room.
      Parameters:
      row - the number of the row of the map that contains this Room.
      col - the number of the column of the map that contains this Room.
      map - the map that contains all the instances of class Room.

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Returns the visual representation of this Room, where the gaps represent the existence of a door.
      Overrides:
      toString in class Object

    • loadMap

      static Room[][] loadMap(int[][][] map)
      Constructs the Room instances of the given map, makes the appropriate connections between the Room instances according to the given map, and returns the map with all the Room instances.
      Parameters:
      map - a 3-dimensional integer array. The element map[i][j] corresponds to the Room instance at (i,j) position of the grid and contains an array of 4 integers. The k-th integer is either 1 or 0 if there is or isn't respectively a door at the Direction constant with ordinal number k.
      Returns:
      the 2-dimensional array-map with all the Room instances.

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Method for testing, loads a sample map and prints all the rooms and the adjacent rooms of a certain room.
